channelName: DLR Institute of Structures and Design
description:
Das Institut für Bauweisen und Strukturtechnologie gehört zum Deutschen Zentrum für Luft- und Raumfahrt (DLR) und entwickelt Hochleistungsstrukturen für viele Anwendungsbereiche (Luft- und Raumfahrt, Verkehr u.a.) von der Konzeption bis zur Produktionstechnologie.
Das Institut verteilt sich auf die zwei Standorte Stuttgart und Augsburg.

In Stuttgart sind vier Abteilungen angesiedelt:
- Bauteilgestaltung und Fertigungstechnologien
- Keramische Verbundstrukturen
- Strukturelle Integrität
- Raumfahrt Systemintegration

In Augsburg befindet sich die Abteilung „Automatisierung und Qualitätssicherung in der Produktion“.
Diese Abteilung ist gleichzeitig das DLR „Zentrum für Leichtbauproduktionstechnologie“ (ZLP) am Standort Augsburg.
https://www.dlr.de/zlp/desktopdefault.aspx/tabid-10812/ 

Impressum:
https://www.dlr.de/bt/desktopdefault.aspx/tabid-2475/

description:
ハヤブサで色々な昆虫を、採集にいきます
あまり積載できないのが難点ですが
高速での移動は超楽チンです

基本　チョウが専門ですが　トンボ、水生昆虫
カブト、クワガタ、標本が専門です。
最近はカマキリも飼育、標本と分野を広げています
外産のカマキリは　超面白い形なので
魅力的ですね。

ハヤブサでいろんな場所に行きます
バイク用品やおすすめのカスタム部品
カスタム箇所などの紹介　バイク関連の動画です
愛知県在住なので近場のビュースポットなども紹介していきたいと思っています。

もう一つは
好きな昆虫を　紹介します

日本の昆虫や世界の昆虫標本
色々な場所での採集

特に最近は水生昆虫の飼育、繁殖に力をいれています
ゲンゴロウの累代飼育
ナミゲンゴロウをメインに
ヒメフチドリゲンゴロウ
エゾゲンゴロウモドキ
クロゲンゴロウ
シマゲンゴロウ
マルガタゲンゴロウなどを繁殖させています

タガメの累代飼育
オニヤンマのヤゴ飼育
マルタンヤンマのヤゴ飼育

飼育下で🌟になってしまった個体の標本作りも
やっています


何年かぶりにヤママユガ採集にも
いっています
ガの世界は奥が深いですね！


冬はもっぱら　標本作りです
チョウの軟化展翅がおもな作業ですね

description:
My channel is a collection of golf swing videos of professional golfers. Most of the videos have been taken with the Casio Exilim EX-FH25 or Sony RX10  IV / RX100 VI cameras (at either 240 or 250 frames-per-second). Normally the videos are taken at a shutter speed of around 1/2500  to give sharpness to the club and hands during the downswing. If better equipment is available I will try it out!

Most of the videos have been taken at European Tour events – mostly UK events - though sometimes I venture out as far as Denmark, Turkey and most recently Australia. All the videos are taken during practice days or pro-ams and are never taken during the tournament days.

Enjoy the videos!

Michael Field

description:
I record videos of events such as cultural celebrations, charity events and Cosplay events. Music videos such as covers. Exhibition events like NAB, CES, PAX East and auto shows. Travel / scenery from the Azores, Portugal, Iceland, Denmark, Las Vegas Nevada, New York, Boston Massachusetts, Phoenix Arizona, etc. 

A lot of times, you'll see mostly photos and some short videos of certain event. With me shooting videos that are much longer than the norm, it's as if you were their. You'll see more of the action. I'm basically shooting live videos of history. I'm sort of an independent journalist that'll cover just about any kind of event no matter what it's about. In the future, I may plan on adding mini comic movies since I have a ton of creative ideas.

Just because I record an event, it doesn't necessarily mean I stand for everything the event is about. I'm just documenting it.

I’ve been passionate about archery since I took my first shot at six years old in Elma, New York. What started as a hobby quickly became a lifelong pursuit — and eventually a profession. On this channel, I focus on in-depth archery tutorials, equipment reviews, tuning guides, and real-world testing—covering everything from Olympic recurve to barebow, traditional, and compound. Whether you’re just getting started or chasing precision, there’s something here for you.

At the core of it all is my personal affirmation:
“I Am. I Am Passion. I Am Growth. I Am an Archer.”

Sri Kumaran Stores’ journey began humbly over half a century ago when Kanjipuram’s P.C

description:
A 100 Acre Permaculture Farm and Nursery located in Damascus, Ontario. Run by two brothers Nick (31) and Taylor (30) -  Check us out on instagram @LutherMarshOrganics  

A farm purchased by our father in 1980, enjoyed on weekends with family to escape the city, eventually moving here full time. My brother and I planted many trees with him throughout the years but only recently dove into the realm of fruit and nut farming. We have many plans for expansion; vegetables, mushrooms, eggs, and pasture raised animals. With 65 acres of pristine pasture (Timothy,Trefoil,Alfalfa) and 35 acres of cedar forest, we have a lot of possibilities. 

Some of the fruit and nut trees we are growing are; Seabuckthorn/Seaberry, Haskaps, Hazelnuts, Heartnuts, Aronia, Elderberry, Hazelnuts, Currants, Chestnuts, Tart Cherries, Mulberries, American Plums, Kiwi Berries, and Paw Paws! Trees can be quite expensive so we are slowly adding to our stock every year!

channelName: Revo Physiotherapy and Sports Performance Denver
description:
Revo PT and Sports Performance Denver is the newest Revo location that opened in early 2023. 

Revo Physiotherapy and Sports Performance was founded in 2015 by physical therapists in Boulder, Colorado looking for an environment to apply their full skill set. Their dream facility blended evidence-based physical therapy, sports performance training, and cutting edge technology to capture objective data for athletes and clients. That dream now exists as Revo.

We believe in the use of diagnostic technology to gather objective data in order to expedite the evaluation and treatment process. Through the use of technology previously reserved for research settings, we can identify movement patterns quickly and accurately. We strive to find the root cause of your pain or performance limitation and fix it.

 We believe that the best physical therapists in the world are able to move seamlessly between rehabilitation and sports performance training with ease.

description:
On the Torque Test Channel our aim is to test old-school to modern tools on a level playing field to compare or reveal performance figures in understandable terms in order to shine some light on recent marketing trends.

FAQ:
You should use ($120-250) battery on (X) brand! 
If they package their kit that way. For now, they rate the tool's specs with the battery they provide so we test vs that. 

What air set-up do you have?
IR 80gal compressor - 20ft 1" cast iron pipe to 3ft 3/4" pipe threaded into wall regulator (48 CFM max), 3/8" NPT out to  3/8" 25ft hose. 1/4" Milton V Hi-Flo Pro fittings and Milton 5in1 hi-flo coupler (67 CFM max)

Why do you test up to 15 seconds (that's too long, too short): 
See ep1, there's a standard for impact testing. 

Can I send you a tool and you send back?
Yes! TorqueTestChannel at gmail.com

Why not use a torque wrench?
See ep3 on nut-busting. 

It's technically "pounds-foot" though
We tried saying it that way, it's pretty laborsome after awhile.

description:
Upon graduation, Ayden Hector Stanford  took the bold step of furthering his education at Colorado State University, Fort Collins, CO. Drawn to the allure of the majestic mountains, he found a perfect blend of natural beauty and academic rigor. Despite the scenic distractions, Ayden, majoring in business, remains a pinnacle of dedication. He expected to graduate early, in December 2023, and his zeal for excellence is evident.

Parallel to his academic strides, his passion for football flourished. His talent shone through as a formidable defensive back for the Colorado State Rams, earning him all-conference honors in just seven games. In the 2022 season, he asserted himself as a pillar of the defense, amassing impressive statistics, including 24 tackles and three interceptions. A memorable highlight was on October 7, 2022; he registered eight tackles and clinched an interception, which he skillfully returned for a touchdown.
